<div id="review_2721188577" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2721188577" />
    <a title="Andrey Pogorelov" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/92627029-andrey-pogorelov"><img alt="Andrey Pogorelov" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1571478526p2/92627029.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2721188577?book_show_action=true">Feb 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andrey Pogorelov" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andrey Pogorelov" href="/user/show/92627029-andrey-pogorelov">Andrey Pogorelov</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover " href="/book/show/24096190">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/92627029-andrey-pogorelov?shelf=2019">2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2721188577" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10739228822119754762">It’s really hard for me to give Chekhov a rating, and 4 stars are just to express my level of excitement and awe compared to some other classics.<br/><br/>I didn’t pay much attention to Chekhov’s works back in school, and I’m pretty sure his drama is way to complicated for kids. Perhaps I will be revisiting his works later on to discover something new about people and life itself.<br/><br/>Chekhov is a true master of drama, and even if you don’t really read much drama (like myself), you should definitely give this </span>
  <span id="freeText10739228822119754762" style="display:none">It’s really hard for me to give Chekhov a rating, and 4 stars are just to express my level of excitement and awe compared to some other classics.<br /><br />I didn’t pay much attention to Chekhov’s works back in school, and I’m pretty sure his drama is way to complicated for kids. Perhaps I will be revisiting his works later on to discover something new about people and life itself.<br /><br />Chekhov is a true master of drama, and even if you don’t really read much drama (like myself), you should definitely give this book a chance, and enjoy some deep real-life characters and great attention to detail.<br /><br />My absolute favorite play of the bunch is “The Cherry Orchard”. It reminds me of a popular British TV show called “Downton Abbey” where an aristocratic family faces the dawn of a new era and has to adapt losing a lot in the process. Chekhov’s plot is pretty similar but more tragic and more “Russian” in a way.<br /><br />Another one I really enjoyed was “The Three Sisters”. It’s about people’s hopes for a better life and defeat thereof. It really got to me in a somewhat disturbing way.<br /><br />Totally recommend if you are interested in theater and drama. The plays are fairly short and easy to read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10739228822119754762" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


