<div id="review_4095452067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4095452067" />
    <a title="Valerie " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64265994-valerie"><img alt="Valerie " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4095452067?book_show_action=true">Jul 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Valerie " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Valerie " href="/user/show/64265994-valerie">Valerie </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6591417-the-four-major-plays">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4095452067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18375717386737964165">Again and again Chekhov writes that life grinds our hopes and dreams into dust. There is little hope nor escape from the misery that is life. His characters seek work, love and other distractions from the inevitability of death. Chekhov is showing us that life is absurd because death renders it ultimately meaningless. <br/>I couldn’t agree more. Whenever I’m asked to state my religious preference I always answer “absurdist.”</span>

          </span>
        </div>


